OL,3,C'Knew the axe would potentially cause
OL,4,Cfatal damage' - Man jailed for wife
OL,5,Cattack
OL,7,FA man from Cumbria who struck his wife
OL,8,Fthree times with a climbing axe
OL,9,Fleaving her with a fractured skull was
OL,10,Fdescribed by police as knowing "the
OL,11,Faxe would cause potentially fatal
OL,12,Fdamage."
OL,14,FDaniel Holden, 56, of Station Road,
OL,15,FKeswick, was jailed for four years for
OL,16,Fgrievous bodily harm with intent at
OL,17,FCarlisle Crown Court on 6 January
OL,18,F2025. He pleaded guilty in November
OL,19,F2024.
